case_circumstances: The skeletal remains of Hispanic male between 35-45-years of age were found in the Tijuana River Valley area of San Diego.  On 09/29/15, a border patrol agent located a tibia, which was initially found weeks prior and discounted as a probable animal bone.  The agent believed it to be human and contacted San Diego Police and the Medical Examiner's Office.  The bone was collected and a search of the area for additional bones was conducted on 09/30/15.  Additional bones were located under the dirt along the wash area.
